{% apply markdown_to_html %}
  Cards are stylized links that can be presented with imagery, text, and
  attribution.
{% endapply %}

{% set variables %}
  {% apply markdown_to_html %}
    | Variable            | Type    | Required | Description                                                                                                            |
    |---------------------|---------|----------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
    | link_url            | url     | true     | The link for the card. This can be internal or external.                                                               |
    | link_text           | string  | true     | The link text for the card. This is displayed and read by A/T as the link label.                                       |
    | link_attribution    | string  | false    | This text is shown below the link.  It is not part of the link label.                                                  |
    | description         | string  | false    | This text is shown below the attribution. It is not part of the link label.                                            |
    | image               | url     | false    | An optional image to display in the card.  Note that either image_alt or image_decorative must be explicitly provided. |
    | image_alt           | string  | false    | The appropriate alternative text to display for the image.                                                             |
    | image_decorative    | boolean | false    | If toggled on, the image will be considered decorative in nature.                                                      |
    | image_overlay_style | enum    | false    | If provided, a context-specific overlay may be applied to the image.                                                   |
    | list                | boolean | false    | If toggled on, the card will render in a configuration appropriate for inclusion in lists.                             |

    ### Accessibility notes
    If an image is provided, either <em>image_alt</em> or
    <em>image_decorative</em> <strong>must</strong> also be specified. It was
    an intentional design decision to force consumers to contemplate the nature
    of the image on a per-card basis. This hopefully prevents misuse of
    alternative text.
  {% endapply %}
{% endset %}

{% set modifiers %}{% apply markdown_to_html %}

  ### Image overlays

  | Overlay       | Description                                                   |
  |---------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
  | video         | Uses an overlay that suggests that the card links to a video. |

  #### Accessibility notes
  If an overlay is used, please ensure that the link text adequately describes
  the nature of the link!

{% endapply %}{% endset %}
